					Full Description



Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation (E&S), incorporated on May 10, 1968, focuses on the production of visual display systems used primarily in full-dome video projection applications, dome projection screens, dome architectural treatments, and content for planetariums, schools, science centers, other educational institutions and entertainment venues. It operates in the visual simulation market segment. The Company, through its subsidiary, Spitz, Inc. (Spitz), is a supplier of planetarium systems, dome projection screens and other dome displays. The Company supplies total system solutions for its digital theater markets, as well as domes and other geometric structures in the architectural market.The Company offers a range of products and services for dome and planetarium theaters in educational institutions, training and entertainment venues. These products include planetarium and dome theater systems consisting of hardware and software, and other visual display systems primarily used to project digital video on curved surfaces. The Company also produces show content both for its own library, which it licenses to customers and for specific customer requirements for planetarium, and dome theaters. Additionally, it manufactures and installs metal domes with customized optical coatings and acoustical properties that are used for planetarium and dome theaters, as well as other custom applications. Its dome engineering and manufacturing resources design and supply geometrically complex structures for customized architectural treatments, often involving curved metal shapes with optical and acoustical properties.Digital TheaterThe Company's digital display systems can be configured with its projector systems or standard commercial projectors. The Company offers Digistar full-dome digital system, along with other customized software tools. Its SciDome planetarium system uses a dome theater version of a retail desktop astronomy product with curriculum tools for teachers.Advanced DisplaysThe Company's products are used for advance display applications for audiences in specialty theaters and other visitor attractions. This includes the integration of the advanced video projectors with lenses, software and application techniques to serve customers in search of display of visual content.Domed StructuresSpitz is a producer of domed projection screens. Through Spitz, the Company designs, manufactures and installs domed projection screens used in planetarium theaters and a range of other applications, such as ride simulators, special or large format film theaters, simulation training systems and architectural treatments. The Company offers dome products, such as its NanoSeam dome. The customers in its dome business are entities in the entertainment, educational, and commercial and military simulation markets. Its customers include theme parks, casinos, world expositions, museums, schools and military defense contractors. In addition, construction or metal fabrication contractors supply domed projection screens in foreign markets.The Company competes with GOTO Optical Mfg. Co., Konica-Minolta Planetarium Co. Ltd., Carl Zeiss Inc. and Sky-Skan, Inc.

» Full Overview of ESCC.PK







