Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation Key Developments

Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation, Annual General Meeting, May 12, 2017
Apr 7 17
Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation, Annual General Meeting, May 12, 2017, at 11:00 Mountain Daylight. Location: 770 Komas Drive Salt Lake City, UT 84108 United States Agenda: To elect two Class III directors to the Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation Board of Directors; to ratify the appointment of Tanner LLC as independent registered public accounting firm of Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation for the fiscal year ending December 31, 2017; to approve, on a non-binding advisory basis, the compensation paid to named executive officers; and to transact such other business as may properly be presented at the annual meeting.


Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation Promotes Paul Dailey as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer
Dec 16 16
Effective as of December 15, 2016, Paul Dailey was promoted by the Board of Directors of Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation to serve as the Company's Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer. Mr. Dailey previously served as the company's Chief Financial Officer.


Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation Announces Management Changes
Sep 6 16
Evans & Sutherland Computer Corporation announced the appointment of Jonathan Shaw as Chief Executive Officer and a member of the Board of Directors in connection with the retirement of David Bateman as the company’s CEO and Board member, and the promotion of Kirk Johnson to President and Chief Operating Officer, both effective immediately. Mr. Johnson will report to Mr. Shaw. As members of the E&S Executive Management Team, they will work closely together on product and strategy development, marketing and sales to drive value to its customers, shareholders and employees. Throughout his career, Mr. Shaw has successfully held senior-level positions in operations, manufacturing, sales, product management, marketing and general management. Mr. Shaw was appointed President and Chief Executive Officer of E&S's subsidiary, Spitz Inc., in November 2001, where he held various management positions since 1985. Prior to Spitz, Jon held several engineering positions with Mobil Oil Corporation. He holds a BS in Engineering from the University of Delaware and an MBA from Widener University. Kirk Johnson will assume the role of President and Chief Operating Officer. Mr. Johnson was appointed Vice President and General Manager of E&S’s Digital Theater Division in 2002. He joined E&S in 1990 and held various engineering and management positions prior to his VP role.


